.TH "set_required_buffer_size" 9 "set_required_buffer_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
set_required_buffer_size \- Sets the buffer size needed for performing IOCTL
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" set_required_buffer_size
.BI "(struct wmi_device *wdev "  ","
.BI "u64 length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "wdev" 12
A wmi bus device from a driver
.IP "length" 12
Required buffer size
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates memory needed for buffer, stores the buffer size in that memory
